  "claim_short": "2109.06338 Kakol Leiderman Michalak A note on Banach spaces E admitting a continuous map from C_p(X) onto E_w Problem 3.10 asks whether there exists a separable Banach space E such that E_w is homeomorphic to C_p[0,1]. Candidate full negative solution: if K is any uncountable compact metrizable C-space, then C_p(K) is not homeomorphic to E_w for any Banach space E. The proof adapts Krupski/Marciszewski/van Mill...",
